In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney discussed a range of topics including President Obama's upcoming address to business leaders, a new report on savings from the Affordable Care Act, the situation in Syria, and the budget. Carney addressed President Putin's op-ed piece in The New York Times, stating that Russia has invested its credibility in the transfer and destruction of Assad's chemical weapons. He also discussed the ongoing diplomatic efforts and the possibility of military assistance to the opposition forces in Syria. On the budget, Carney emphasized the importance of passing a clean continuing resolution and not attaching politically motivated riders to funding bills. He also expressed concern about a potential government shutdown and the need for Congress to fund the government responsibly.